# receive.link routing. NO "/*" catch-all (it shadows real assets: /dist/*.js + /style.css would all
# serve the /app HTML page, breaking every bundle). The app (app.html -> clean URL /app) owns the
# explicit functional routes the Worker emails or app.ts dispatches: /confirm, /revoke, /qr, /d/<id>,
# and /u (the upload view; a share-link open /#code is bounced to /u client-side, code staying in the
# hash). Real assets serve themselves; the marketing homepage owns "/"; unknown paths 404.
/confirm   /app      200
/revoke    /app      200
/qr        /app      200
/d/*       /app      200
/u         /app      200
/          /home/    200
